I live in san diego, and moved here from Connecticut a few years back. My partner and I make crosscountry drives a lot for fam back home, and really, winter driving over on this side of the country is no joke. We even have a awd subie with snow tires when we do it and still. It's scary sometimes, and plans always change because the weather always has a different idea. Just go with the flow and dont panic and recognize it's all apart of the journey.
Stay safe ❤️
